  "name": "DNA Mismatch Repair (MMR)",
  "notGates": 6,
  "notes": "Comprehensive model of E. coli mismatch repair showing the complete MutHLS pathway with critical strand discrimination via Dam methylation. Includes 5 AND gates demonstrating sophisticated multi-protein coordination. Paul Modrich won 2015 Nobel Prize for this work. Essential for publication as MMR defects cause Lynch syndrome cancer in humans - demonstrates medical relevance of bacterial paradigms.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_dna_replication_elongation",
    "ecoli_base_excision_repair",
    "ecoli_nucleotide_excision_repair",
    "ecoli_recombination"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on extensive genetic and biochemical characterization of the E. coli MutHLS system. All protein components, recognition specificities, and directional mechanisms have been validated against primary research. The model represents the paradigm for prokaryotic MMR, which laid the foundation for understanding eukaryotic MMR and its connection to cancer (Lynch syndrome).",
